I'm sorry for wasting my chance.

17
00:00:36.360 --> 00:00:38.640
"How effectively you serve

18
00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:40.950
will determine if you can win or not."

19
00:00:41.720 --> 00:00:45.800
I heard your direction during the 
Fukurodani match and understood it...

20
00:00:46.230 --> 00:00:48.230
And I understood my role.

21
00:00:49.090 --> 00:00:52.420
And then I thought I wanted 
to be able to fight, too...

22
00:00:54.180 --> 00:00:55.140
But...

23
00:00:55.810 --> 00:00:57.320
I ran away at the last minute.

24
00:01:01.570 --> 00:01:02.440
Please...

25
00:01:03.830 --> 00:01:05.590
Give me one more chance.

26
00:01:07.980 --> 00:01:10.420
Oh, shut up already. I know.

27
00:01:20.400 --> 00:01:22.100
Please put me in.

28
00:01:38.410 --> 00:01:44.910
Haikyu!!

29
00:02:54.360 --> 00:02:56.700
Kyotani, get one more in!

30
00:03:03.460 --> 00:03:04.800
Sorry! It's long!

31
00:03:04.800 --> 00:03:05.780
Mattsun!

32
00:03:06.330 --> 00:03:10.080
Episode 22: "The Former Coward's Fight"

33
00:03:07.490 --> 00:03:10.080
All right!

34
00:03:08.790 --> 00:03:10.080
it. Sorry!

35
00:03:10.080 --> 00:03:13.040
Aoba Johsai                Karasuno

36
00:03:10.690 --> 00:03:13.040
This isn't good.

37
00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:15.070
Seijoh's #16 is finding his groove.

38
00:03:13.040 --> 00:03:15.640
Great, great, Issei! Push it, 
push it, Issei! One more time!

39
00:03:15.070 --> 00:03:16.670
They're ahead by five...

40
00:03:16.670 --> 00:03:18.760
Karasuno, fight!

41
00:03:19.080 --> 00:03:20.700
Let's move back a little.

42
00:03:20.700 --> 00:03:23.170
He's probably not going to drop it up front.

43
00:03:23.170 --> 00:03:24.040
Yeah.

44
00:03:24.040 --> 00:03:24.720
Right.

45
00:03:25.880 --> 00:03:27.180
Nice serve!

46
00:03:25.970 --> 00:03:28.720
Bring it, bring it, bring it...

47
00:03:30.140 --> 00:03:31.350
Tanaka!

48
00:03:31.350 --> 00:03:32.440
Yeah!

49
00:03:36.320 --> 00:03:37.900
Yeah!

50
00:03:37.900 --> 00:03:40.610
Aoba Johsai             Karasuno

51
00:03:38.200 --> 00:03:40.610
It's only just begun!

52
00:03:42.190 --> 00:03:43.820
Shoyo, nice serve!

53
00:03:44.600 --> 00:03:46.190
Hey! That guy...

54
00:03:49.800 --> 00:03:52.330
Pardon me. We're switching players.

55
00:03:55.750 --> 00:03:58.650
Oh, there he is. The scaredy cat pinch server.

56
00:03:58.650 --> 00:04:01.970
Right. The guy who was in 
the match with Wakunan, too.

57
00:04:02.300 --> 00:04:04.720
Though I totally understand 
getting freaked out.

58
00:04:04.720 --> 00:04:07.680
I would hate having to serve during a pinch.

59
00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.420
He's the one that got all stiff and 
failed miserably last time, right?

60
00:04:12.420 --> 00:04:13.520
Yeah...

61
00:04:13.520 --> 00:04:16.050
Yamaguchi, get 10 points!

62
00:04:16.050 --> 00:04:17.980
That'd end the match...

63
00:04:18.740 --> 00:04:19.690
I'd forgive you.

64
00:04:23.480 --> 00:04:25.770
G-Give it to 'em good, Yamaguchi!

65
00:04:25.770 --> 00:04:28.720
R-Remain calm... Calm.

66
00:04:28.720 --> 00:04:29.850
Nice serve!

67
00:04:29.850 --> 00:04:30.870
Nice serve.

68
00:04:31.380 --> 00:04:32.890
Give it your all!

69
00:04:32.890 --> 00:04:33.710
Right!

70
00:04:34.830 --> 00:04:36.460
One, and...

71
00:04:37.080 --> 00:04:39.880
Yamaguchi, one more! Nice serve!

72
00:04:44.570 --> 00:04:45.930
Eight seconds...

73
00:04:47.110 --> 00:04:52.270
You know there's time after the 
whistle blows for you to serve, right?

74
00:04:52.270 --> 00:04:53.290
Yes.

75
00:04:53.290 --> 00:04:56.120
You basically get freaked 
out by the whistle and then

76
00:04:56.120 --> 00:04:57.690
do your serve toss almost every time.

77
00:05:00.550 --> 00:05:02.200
Don't be so panicky.

78
00:05:02.920 --> 00:05:04.000
Yes...

79
00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:05.780
Well, all that's left is this.

80
00:05:06.550 --> 00:05:08.580
You went to Ukai's, right?

81
00:05:09.640 --> 00:05:10.580
Yes.

82
00:05:11.300 --> 00:05:12.700
On your own.

83
00:05:14.120 --> 00:05:19.630
Then you're already a 
completely different player.

84
00:05:20.710 --> 00:05:24.860
Go out there and do 
what you want to do.

85
00:05:33.640 --> 00:05:37.480
All of their players have the 
nerve to get serious...

86
00:06:04.420 --> 00:06:05.260
Out!

87
00:06:20.980 --> 00:06:23.690
All right!

88
00:06:23.690 --> 00:06:25.650
All...

89
00:06:25.650 --> 00:06:27.860
...right!

90
00:06:27.860 --> 00:06:29.210
He did it...

91
00:06:29.210 --> 00:06:30.990
Tadashi!

92
00:06:29.640 --> 00:06:30.990
Nice serve!

93
00:06:30.990 --> 00:06:32.990
It got in!

94
00:06:34.530 --> 00:06:35.840
We're...

95
00:06:35.840 --> 00:06:37.530
...supposed to be...

96
00:06:37.530 --> 00:06:39.000
...cheering for Aoba Johsai.

97
00:06:39.000 --> 00:06:41.620
Wait, what? Isn't that a bit overboard?

98
00:06:39.370 --> 00:06:41.000
Yamaguchi, nice serve!

99
00:06:41.620 --> 00:06:43.210
That's just one point.

100
00:06:43.210 --> 00:06:45.830
That's it! Get one more!

101
00:06:51.940 --> 00:06:54.220
A no-touch ace!

102
00:06:54.660 --> 00:06:56.780
Go and catch up!

103
00:06:57.440 --> 00:06:58.720
I'm sorry.

104
00:06:58.720 --> 00:07:00.600
Don't mind! Don't worry about it.

105
00:07:00.880 --> 00:07:05.260
It changed a lot... 
Even I thought it was out.

106
00:07:05.260 --> 00:07:08.320
This is why I hate jump floats.

107
00:07:08.760 --> 00:07:11.580
That was awesome, Yamaguchi! 
Why, you little...

108
00:07:11.580 --> 00:07:13.050
R-Right...

109
00:07:13.050 --> 00:07:15.390
It's not that surprising.

110
00:07:16.400 --> 00:07:17.720
There you go again...

111
00:07:17.720 --> 00:07:19.000
In these five months,

112
00:07:19.460 --> 00:07:22.460
he practiced serving more than anyone else.

113
00:07:26.860 --> 00:07:28.920
Why you little...

114
00:07:28.920 --> 00:07:31.090
Aoba Johsai                         Karasuno

115
00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:31.090
Yamaguchi, one more!

116
00:07:31.600 --> 00:07:33.440
Give it all you've got!

117
00:07:33.440 --> 00:07:35.770
Give it all you've got, Yamaguchi!

118
00:07:35.770 --> 00:07:36.950
He'll be fine.

119
00:07:38.010 --> 00:07:41.890
You always feel worse 
after you run away.

120
00:07:43.520 --> 00:07:47.060
I'm pretty sure Yamaguchi 
feels that way, too.

121
00:07:49.110 --> 00:07:52.460
A shot to break through the skin...

122
00:07:52.460 --> 00:07:54.570
Yeah, and...

123
00:07:55.570 --> 00:07:57.620
The start of our counterattack.

124
00:07:59.020 --> 00:07:59.980
Cut it off!

125
00:07:59.980 --> 00:08:00.790
Yeah.

126
00:08:03.030 --> 00:08:06.460
In volleyball, where it's important 
to connect with your teammates,

127
00:08:06.460 --> 00:08:08.990
the serve is the only solitary play.

128
00:08:08.990 --> 00:08:09.960
Yeah...

129
00:08:10.330 --> 00:08:14.920
It can also be said that it's the only play 
where you can score on your own.

130
00:08:16.680 --> 00:08:19.150
As volleyball evolved,

131
00:08:19.150 --> 00:08:23.110
the serve's power and motive has 
evolved more than anything else.

132
00:08:23.620 --> 00:08:26.400
And in modern volleyball, 
the serve is a powerful attack

133
00:08:27.300 --> 00:08:31.360
that won't get caught by the 
wall known as the block.

134
00:08:33.070 --> 00:08:34.200
Kyotani!

135
00:08:41.720 --> 00:08:42.910
!

136
00:08:44.590 --> 00:08:47.830
A s-second service ace!

137
00:08:48.280 --> 00:08:49.340
Yes!

138
00:08:49.340 --> 00:08:51.470
All right!

139
00:08:52.430 --> 00:08:54.510
Yamaguchi!

140
00:08:52.880 --> 00:08:54.010
Nice serve.

141
00:08:54.510 --> 00:08:57.220
What the heck is that serve? 
That was awesome.

142
00:08:54.940 --> 00:08:57.220
Yamaguchi-kun!

143
00:08:57.530 --> 00:08:58.910
Yamaguchi!

144
00:08:58.910 --> 00:09:00.430
One more!

145
00:09:01.890 --> 00:09:03.600
Bring it!

146
00:09:07.270 --> 00:09:08.330
Got it!

147
00:09:08.330 --> 00:09:09.440
You catch jump floats

148
00:09:09.760 --> 00:09:11.940
with an over-handed hit!

149
00:09:12.360 --> 00:09:13.540
Makki, nice.

150
00:09:15.150 --> 00:09:17.410
He picked it up! They're going to attack.

151
00:09:18.070 --> 00:09:22.740
This fear when you change from being the hunter to becoming the hunted...

152
00:09:24.330 --> 00:09:25.440
Iwaizumi!

153
00:09:27.500 --> 00:09:29.210
He received it with his body?!

154
00:09:30.680 --> 00:09:32.420
Not yet... Not yet.

155
00:09:33.880 --> 00:09:35.840
I'm not going to let you serve just yet!

156
00:09:38.060 --> 00:09:40.380
Cover!

157
00:09:41.280 --> 00:09:42.470
Thanks, Kageyama...

158
00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:44.430
Tsukishima, get the last!

159
00:09:49.990 --> 00:09:51.770
All right!

160
00:09:52.600 --> 00:09:53.640
Tsukki...

161
00:09:52.600 --> 00:09:54.030
A wipe!

162
00:09:54.030 --> 00:09:56.530
They used that block really well.

163
00:09:54.460 --> 00:09:55.850
Tsukishima!

164
00:09:56.530 --> 00:09:59.240
Aoba Johsai                             Karasuno

165
00:09:56.910 --> 00:09:58.520
Now they've gotten three consecutive points.

166
00:10:03.970 --> 00:10:05.080
One more.

167
00:10:09.060 --> 00:10:09.750
Yeah!

168
00:10:12.080 --> 00:10:14.700
Oh? Seijoh's taking a time out.

169
00:10:14.700 --> 00:10:17.090
They're physically stopping the momentum.

170
00:10:17.090 --> 00:10:19.470
All right!

171
00:10:19.800 --> 00:10:23.200
Making Seijoh take a time out 
is amazing, Yamaguchi!

172
00:10:23.200 --> 00:10:24.870
Yamaguchi!

173
00:10:23.380 --> 00:10:25.310
Th-Thank you...

174
00:10:25.630 --> 00:10:29.390
That #12... made a really bold receive.

175
00:10:29.390 --> 00:10:31.520
That was just luck, though.

176
00:10:34.930 --> 00:10:36.150
Wow...

177
00:10:37.330 --> 00:10:38.310
It hurts a lot...

178
00:10:39.460 --> 00:10:41.450
All right! Let's win this!

179
00:10:41.820 --> 00:10:43.910
Keep it up!

180
00:10:44.830 --> 00:10:49.920
I want to be able to control 
my body like the other guys!

181
00:10:49.920 --> 00:10:51.880
I want to be able to control the ball!

182
00:10:51.880 --> 00:10:54.390
I want to fight head-on 
with strong opponents!

183
00:10:56.670 --> 00:10:58.300
All right!

184
00:10:58.620 --> 00:10:59.850
Yamaguchi!

185
00:10:59.850 --> 00:11:01.510
One more!

186
00:11:01.850 --> 00:11:03.530
Keep your eye on the ball!

187
00:11:03.530 --> 00:11:04.220
Right!

188
00:11:10.400 --> 00:11:11.730
Listen up, Tadashi.

189
00:11:12.670 --> 00:11:15.710
You can't give them the 
chance to take the ball.

190
00:11:15.710 --> 00:11:19.400
Aim straight through, as close 
as you can get to the white...

191
00:11:21.290 --> 00:11:22.110
...and hit!

192
00:11:28.100 --> 00:11:30.040
I only have one weapon:

193
00:11:31.680 --> 00:11:32.620
my serve.

194
00:11:34.520 --> 00:11:38.540
The chance I received
is just one service chance.

195
00:11:39.680 --> 00:11:45.970
I'm going to fight putting my pride and 
the flow of the game into that shot.

196
00:11:46.980 --> 00:11:47.930
I am...

197
00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:56.420
a pinch server.

198
00:11:58.830 --> 00:12:00.990
It's in!

199
00:12:01.280 --> 00:12:02.800
Is luck on our side now?

200
00:12:02.800 --> 00:12:04.830
No, it's not just that.

201
00:12:06.600 --> 00:12:07.560
Now...

202
00:12:08.080 --> 00:12:12.540
Aoba Johsai               Karasuno

203
00:12:09.480 --> 00:12:10.820
We're tied.

204
00:12:12.580 --> 00:12:19.550
Haikyu!!

205
00:12:19.590 --> 00:12:26.550
Haikyu!!

206
00:12:26.550 --> 00:12:31.770
Aoba Johsai               Karasuno

207
00:12:28.070 --> 00:12:29.600
Now they're tied!

208
00:12:29.600 --> 00:12:31.100
Karasuno caught up!

209
00:12:32.400 --> 00:12:34.700
Yamaguchi!

210
00:12:32.400 --> 00:12:36.520
That same net drop happened during 
the Wakunan match, too, right?

211
00:12:36.520 --> 00:12:38.520
Tadashi's a lucky boy!

212
00:12:38.520 --> 00:12:39.920
Yup, yup!

213
00:12:39.920 --> 00:12:41.720
It might be a net drop,

214
00:12:41.720 --> 00:12:44.990
but it's completely different from 
the one during the Wakunan match.

215
00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:47.210
During the Wakunan match,

216
00:12:45.640 --> 00:12:47.710
Yamagauchi, one more!

217
00:12:47.210 --> 00:12:51.940
Tadashi was thinking about whether
or not the ball would go in.

218
00:12:47.710 --> 00:12:49.830
Yamaguchi, nice serve!

219
00:12:52.390 --> 00:12:53.960
Right now, he's thinking about

220
00:12:54.820 --> 00:12:56.300
where he's going to serve it.

221
00:12:57.120 --> 00:13:00.460
This net drop was a result 
of switching to offense.

222
00:13:02.670 --> 00:13:04.790
How awesome, Tadashi!

223
00:13:02.670 --> 00:13:07.340
Though I'm sure he's entirely
 comfortable with that.

224
00:13:08.540 --> 00:13:10.330
One more, Yamaguchi!

225
00:13:09.040 --> 00:13:11.500
The serve toss keeps getting really low.

226
00:13:12.310 --> 00:13:13.770
Right!

227
00:13:14.930 --> 00:13:15.980
Let's calm down, now.

228
00:13:16.380 --> 00:13:17.600
I am calm.

229
00:13:17.600 --> 00:13:20.060
That one couldn't be helped.

230
00:13:20.060 --> 00:13:21.160
We'll get the next one.

231
00:13:21.160 --> 00:13:22.720
That's it, you guys!

232
00:13:22.720 --> 00:13:25.200
You guys are too great.
It makes your captain sad.

233
00:13:41.590 --> 00:13:43.260
It's got a loose spin!

234
00:13:43.260 --> 00:13:44.460
It's not changing direction!

235
00:13:44.460 --> 00:13:45.630
Got it!

236
00:13:46.320 --> 00:13:47.970
Nice receive!

237
00:13:52.520 --> 00:13:53.220
One-touch!

238
00:13:53.480 --> 00:13:54.600
Nice one-touch!

239
00:13:56.900 --> 00:13:58.110
Azumane-san!

240
00:13:58.110 --> 00:13:59.230
Nice, Kageyama!

241
00:14:00.280 --> 00:14:01.230
Three blockers!

242
00:14:01.560 --> 00:14:03.440
And a very high block...

243
00:14:06.860 --> 00:14:08.570
Back!

244
00:14:09.090 --> 00:14:11.260
Out!

245
00:14:13.030 --> 00:14:14.580
All right!

246
00:14:14.990 --> 00:14:17.080
Tanaka, nice call!

247
00:14:14.990 --> 00:14:17.430
H-Hey, seriously?

248
00:14:17.430 --> 00:14:18.540
They...

249
00:14:18.540 --> 00:14:22.250
Aoba Johsai                          Karasuno

250
00:14:19.760 --> 00:14:21.770
Karasuno's at match point!

251
00:14:22.790 --> 00:14:24.060
One more! Nice serve!

252
00:14:24.060 --> 00:14:25.460
Yamaguchi-kun...

253
00:14:26.210 --> 00:14:28.440
...is the hero of this match.

254
00:14:29.430 --> 00:14:30.810
Just one more point...

255
00:14:31.250 --> 00:14:33.140
Just one more point and we win!

256
00:14:33.620 --> 00:14:36.240
Get it in! Please, get it in!

257
00:14:36.240 --> 00:14:37.350
Tadashi!

258
00:14:37.350 --> 00:14:40.840
Yamaguchi! Just one more!

259
00:14:40.840 --> 00:14:42.940
Get it in there!

260
00:14:52.880 --> 00:14:54.120
Feels good...

261
00:14:57.130 --> 00:14:58.290
I'll get it!

262
00:15:00.310 --> 00:15:01.830
it, they're good.

263
00:15:00.310 --> 00:15:01.830
Nice, Watacchi!

264
00:15:07.740 --> 00:15:09.670
Stop it!

265
00:15:07.740 --> 00:15:09.670
Stop it, please!

266
00:15:14.080 --> 00:15:15.810
All right!

267
00:15:16.110 --> 00:15:17.750
Nice kill!

268
00:15:16.110 --> 00:15:21.930
Great, great, Hajime! Push it, 
push it, Hajime! One more time!

269
00:15:16.660 --> 00:15:18.170
We finally cut it off...

270
00:15:18.170 --> 00:15:20.520
How many points did he get, anyway?

271
00:15:28.200 --> 00:15:30.240
That was magnificent!

272
00:15:30.240 --> 00:15:31.230
Good job!

273
00:15:31.230 --> 00:15:32.570
Thank you.

274
00:15:32.570 --> 00:15:34.650
You did great, Yamaguchi!

275
00:15:33.230 --> 00:15:34.270
All right!

276
00:15:34.270 --> 00:15:35.020
Thanks!

277
00:15:34.650 --> 00:15:36.030
That was awesome!

278
00:15:37.320 --> 00:15:38.870
Concentrate on the one!

279
00:15:39.350 --> 00:15:40.310
Next time,

280
00:15:42.150 --> 00:15:43.480
I'll get 10 points.

281
00:15:45.960 --> 00:15:47.260
I'm not gonna lose!

282
00:15:49.170 --> 00:15:50.860
Hanamaki, nice serve!

283
00:15:49.780 --> 00:15:51.630
The chance that Yamaguchi gave us...

284
00:15:54.000 --> 00:15:55.080
Daichi-san!

285
00:15:55.080 --> 00:15:56.710
We're not gonna let it go to waste!

286
00:15:59.610 --> 00:16:01.230
All right!

287
00:16:01.520 --> 00:16:03.190
Nice, Azumane!

288
00:16:03.470 --> 00:16:05.080
They're there again!

289
00:16:05.080 --> 00:16:06.400
Match point!

290
00:16:06.400 --> 00:16:08.820
Go!

291
00:16:12.850 --> 00:16:14.190
All right!

292
00:16:14.190 --> 00:16:16.320
They got it back so easily.

293
00:16:16.320 --> 00:16:19.640
They managed a quick even though 
they're being cornered right now.

294
00:16:20.020 --> 00:16:22.120
Not to mention, right up front.

295
00:16:22.540 --> 00:16:25.000
If it were me, I'd be relying on the ace.

296
00:16:25.000 --> 00:16:26.000
Yeah!

297
00:16:26.000 --> 00:16:27.960
Aoba Johsai                  Karasuno

298
00:16:28.710 --> 00:16:29.960
Nice receive!

299
00:16:29.960 --> 00:16:30.920
There're two!

300
00:16:33.380 --> 00:16:34.810
All right!

301
00:16:34.810 --> 00:16:36.410
Tsukishima, nice kill!

302
00:16:35.650 --> 00:16:38.110
Hey, your movements are stiff, Kindaichi.

303
00:16:38.110 --> 00:16:39.480
Yes! No!

304
00:16:39.480 --> 00:16:40.470
Which is it?

305
00:16:41.220 --> 00:16:42.970
This is a critical moment for us.

306
00:16:43.540 --> 00:16:47.440
We can't make this the
 third-years' last match.

307
00:16:47.440 --> 00:16:49.690
Don't think about anything unnecessary.

308
00:16:50.780 --> 00:16:53.720
No matter what, you only need to focus on

309
00:16:53.720 --> 00:16:55.260
the ball in front of you.

310
00:16:56.360 --> 00:16:57.160
Right!

311
00:16:57.160 --> 00:16:59.230
Asahi, get this!

312
00:16:59.230 --> 00:17:00.700
Nice serve!

313
00:17:07.340 --> 00:17:08.840
It's long! Get this!

314
00:17:13.800 --> 00:17:19.340
Great, great, Yutaro. Push it, 
push it, Yutaro! One more time!

315
00:17:14.190 --> 00:17:15.720
All right!

316
00:17:15.720 --> 00:17:16.760
Nice kill!

317
00:17:16.760 --> 00:17:17.840
Thanks!

318
00:17:18.190 --> 00:17:20.140
I guess that's to be expected of Seijoh.

319
00:17:20.140 --> 00:17:22.920
The next one is going to be huge.

320
00:17:22.920 --> 00:17:23.810
But...

321
00:17:27.120 --> 00:17:28.190
And...

322
00:17:29.560 --> 00:17:33.570
...in modern volleyball, the 
serve is a powerful attack

323
00:17:34.740 --> 00:17:37.280
that won't get caught by

324
00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:44.760
the wall known as the block.

325
00:18:03.510 --> 00:18:05.140
That was basically a spike...

326
00:18:07.130 --> 00:18:09.060
All right!

327
00:18:09.060 --> 00:18:12.480
All right!

328
00:18:12.480 --> 00:18:15.440
Great, great, Toru! Push it, 
push it, Toru! One more time!

329
00:18:15.440 --> 00:18:19.910
Aoba Johsai                      Karasuno

330
00:18:15.710 --> 00:18:18.050
Seijoh turned it around into a set point!

331
00:18:18.050 --> 00:18:19.910
Are they going to get the set?

332
00:18:19.910 --> 00:18:22.370
!

333
00:18:22.950 --> 00:18:25.330
This isn't possible with just the two of us.

334
00:18:27.230 --> 00:18:29.470
Asahi, please. We're counting on you.

335
00:18:29.470 --> 00:18:30.280
Yeah.

336
00:18:30.840 --> 00:18:33.250
Azumane-kun's going to be 
receiving the serve, too?

337
00:18:33.530 --> 00:18:35.690
If that's what Sawamura and 
Nishinoya decided,

338
00:18:35.690 --> 00:18:37.340
then that's probably best.

339
00:18:37.830 --> 00:18:42.380
It appears that Oikawa's serves 
focus more on power than control.

340
00:18:43.270 --> 00:18:45.080
Rather than them scoring a no-touch,

341
00:18:45.080 --> 00:18:49.050
touching and getting the ball 
up in any way is better.

342
00:18:50.770 --> 00:18:54.900
We received plenty of Ubugawa's 
and Fukurodani's serves.

343
00:18:55.650 --> 00:18:57.770
It's okay. We can fight.

344
00:18:58.960 --> 00:19:00.820
Bring it!

345
00:19:01.280 --> 00:19:03.030
Nice serve!

346
00:19:11.690 --> 00:19:12.620
Daichi-san!

347
00:19:13.680 --> 00:19:14.620
Good!

348
00:19:19.160 --> 00:19:20.380
Tanaka, nice!

349
00:19:20.380 --> 00:19:21.590
Kageyama!

350
00:19:21.880 --> 00:19:22.640
Asahi!

351
00:19:22.640 --> 00:19:23.780
Asahi-san!

352
00:19:26.010 --> 00:19:27.470
Nice receive!

353
00:19:40.990 --> 00:19:42.910
All right!

354
00:19:42.910 --> 00:19:45.370
Aoba Johsai                 Karasuno

355
00:19:45.880 --> 00:19:47.770
They got the set back.

356
00:19:47.770 --> 00:19:50.080
I thought Karasuno was just 
going to win straight through.

357
00:19:50.950 --> 00:19:52.520
And we had them cornered!

358
00:19:52.520 --> 00:19:53.520
Don't mind!

359
00:19:53.520 --> 00:19:54.970
We're just getting started!

360
00:19:54.970 --> 00:19:58.050
! That third set is gonna be rough!

361
00:19:58.410 --> 00:19:59.560
Let's change it up!

362
00:19:59.560 --> 00:20:00.260
Right!

363
00:20:00.560 --> 00:20:03.060
His serve really is amazing.

364
00:20:03.800 --> 00:20:06.030
You were awesome, too, Yamaguchi.

365
00:20:06.030 --> 00:20:08.140
He's much more experienced than I am.

366
00:20:09.090 --> 00:20:11.720
That might be obvious 
because he's a third-year,

367
00:20:11.720 --> 00:20:13.770
but I don't think that's the only thing.

368
00:20:13.770 --> 00:20:15.220
Not the only thing?

369
00:20:16.170 --> 00:20:20.490
A jump serve is a serve that balances 
a lot of power with a high risk.

370
00:20:21.490 --> 00:20:22.860
To be able to add force to his serve

371
00:20:23.410 --> 00:20:26.240
and still have it land in when they 
were cornered like that...

372
00:20:30.770 --> 00:20:32.120
He's something special.

373
00:20:33.760 --> 00:20:35.330
Yamaguchi!

374
00:20:35.760 --> 00:20:37.240
Those were nice serves!

375
00:20:37.240 --> 00:20:38.580
Th-Thanks.

376
00:20:38.980 --> 00:20:41.020
But I've still got a ways to go.

377
00:20:42.240 --> 00:20:45.220
Only half of my serves were any good.

378
00:20:45.960 --> 00:20:49.610
Then be super happy about 
the half that were good!

379
00:20:50.980 --> 00:20:54.220
Even if you put aside regret, 
you'll end up feeling it anyway.

380
00:20:54.640 --> 00:20:57.340
Right now, you need to make sure 
you grasp this good feeling

381
00:20:57.340 --> 00:20:58.940
and never forget it.

382
00:20:58.940 --> 00:21:00.110
Grasp really hard.

383
00:21:00.440 --> 00:21:02.820
And do it again next time, too.

384
00:21:06.360 --> 00:21:07.180
Yes!

385
00:21:09.790 --> 00:21:11.580
So we ended up getting a full set...

386
00:21:15.920 --> 00:21:17.760
Our first practice match,

387
00:21:26.150 --> 00:21:27.510
the Inter-High prelims...

388
00:21:35.560 --> 00:21:36.900
And now...

389
00:21:44.910 --> 00:21:47.130
We're having our most intense match yet.

390
00:21:50.740 --> 00:21:51.910
Difficult opponents...

391
00:21:53.150 --> 00:21:54.660
Troublesome opponents...

392
00:21:56.130 --> 00:21:58.920
We didn't even have much of a connection 
with them until last year...

393
00:22:00.230 --> 00:22:02.420
They were supposed to be beneath us...

394
00:22:04.500 --> 00:22:07.420
But apparently we're fated 
to play to the fullest.

395
00:22:08.380 --> 00:22:11.100
Aoba Johsai                          Karasuno

396
00:22:09.350 --> 00:22:11.100
The final set...

397
00:22:11.100 --> 00:22:15.560
Rule the Court

398
00:22:11.100 --> 00:22:15.560
Fly

399
00:22:12.240 --> 00:22:14.070
This is our last battle!

400
00:23:46.360 --> 00:23:48.080
That was amazing, Yamaguchi-kun!

401
00:23:48.080 --> 00:23:49.240
Th-Thank you very much, Yachi-san.

402
00:23:49.240 --> 00:23:54.090
Just in case, I had an AED, 
stretcher, and coffin prepared,

403
00:23:54.090 --> 00:23:55.660
but they weren't necessary at all!

404
00:23:55.660 --> 00:23:58.080
Huh?! Wasn't there something that 
didn't belong at the end there?

405
00:23:56.950 --> 00:24:00.540
Episode 23: "Team"

406
00:23:58.080 --> 00:24:00.040
Next time on Haikyu!!:"Team."
